          <avActivityHighlights>Wind slabs and wet snow represent the main danger.</avActivityHighlights>
          <avActivityComment>As a consequence of new snow and wind individual small to medium-sized slab avalanches are possible above approximately 1300 m. &lt;br/&gt; In the vicinity of peaks a dangerous avalanche situation will be encountered in some localities. The more recent wind slabs and can be released easily. &lt;br/&gt; Avalanches can penetrate down to the ground and reach medium size in some cases.</avActivityComment>
          <snowpackStructureComment>The weather conditions as the day progresses will give rise to unfavourable bonding of the snowpack in some places. &lt;br/&gt;</snowpackStructureComment>
